solution: ```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    int maximumXOR(vector<int>& nums) {
        int res = 0;
        for (int v : nums) res |= v;
        return res;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The operation can turn any bit in nums[i] to 0 but never to 1, so the final XOR is maximized when every bit that can be 1 is 1. The bitwise OR of all numbers gives exactly that set of bits, which is the maximum achievable XOR.

